<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sorega}}}} is an interjection used to signal that the speaker is about to provide an unexpected response to a question.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A: @HI{{@KJ{{test^verification}},doudatta?}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B: @HI{{@EM{{sorega}},damedattanda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td> 
      A: How was the exam?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td> 
      B: Well, it didn't go well.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
When an interjection is used, @HI{{@EM{{sorega}}}} follows it.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A: @HI{{@KJ{{come^year}}ha@KJ{{day^hon}}de@KJ{{work}}kundesune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B: @HI{{iya,@EM{{sorega}}@KJ{{going}}kenakunatteshimattandesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td> 
      A: You're going to work in japan next year, aren't you?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td> 
      B: Well, no, it turns out that I can't go.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

